SCOPE & EXPORT NOTICE
=====================

Scope: industrial / civilian cooperative-UAV operation.

This project implements cooperative-fleet coordination for civilian missions
(search-and-rescue, infrastructure inspection, agriculture, mapping, telecom relay):

  - formation keeping (virtual structure, leader-follower, Reynolds flocking)
  - collision avoidance (RRT-APF reactive planning)
  - distributed consensus (Raft) and gossip/mesh state sharing
  - cooperative task allocation (auction / FNN bid scoring)
  - cooperative-navigation reinforcement learning (MAPPO)

It does NOT implement, and is not intended for:

  - adaptive behavior in response to threats or mission objectives
  - target acquisition, tracking-to-engage, or fire control
  - weapons integration or munitions deployment
  - autonomous engagement / countermeasure behavior

Per the U.S. State Department's clarification distinguishing cooperative and
formation operation from military "swarming" (adaptive behavior in response to
threats or mission objectives), the maintainer's assessment is that these
capabilities fall OUTSIDE USML Category VIII(h)(12).

This NOTICE is not legal advice and is not an export-control determination.
Final classification (USML / ITAR / EAR) is the responsibility of the maintainer
and qualified export counsel. Any downstream modification that adds adaptive
threat/mission-response behavior may change this classification.
